WEBVTT

00:02.680 --> 00:04.547
[ Wind Whistling ]

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:22.447 --> 00:24.780
[ Man ]
Viewer, beware.

00:24.780 --> 00:27.713
You're in for a scare.

00:27.713 --> 00:30.713
Goosebumps.

00:33.313 --> 00:35.147
[ Thunderclap ]

00:39.380 --> 00:41.613
[ Male Voice ]
Riley.

00:48.847 --> 00:51.313
[ Crying, Panting ]

00:51.313 --> 00:53.180
[ Creaking ]

00:53.180 --> 00:54.680
[ Screaming ]

00:57.980 --> 01:00.113
You're home early.

01:00.113 --> 01:02.947
You should be congratulating me
on my creativity.

01:02.947 --> 01:06.480
Most brothers would have just jumped
out of the closet and yelled "Boo."

01:06.480 --> 01:09.247
- You scared poor Riley to death.
- Come on, Mom.

01:09.247 --> 01:12.047
You're not really gonna
send me away, are you?

01:12.547 --> 01:14.647
Did you read the brochure?

01:14.647 --> 01:16.080
"The Perfect School.

01:16.080 --> 01:18.947
Why settle for anything
less than perfect?"

01:19.380 --> 01:21.180
Good luck, son.

01:22.147 --> 01:23.947
Goodbye, sweetie.

01:23.947 --> 01:27.447
[ Mom ] I hope you learn
something from this experience.

01:27.447 --> 01:29.880
[ Headmaster ] Gentlemen,
your days of disobedience

01:29.880 --> 01:31.813
and troublemaking
have come to an end.

01:31.813 --> 01:35.847
From this moment forward, you'll do
what you are told, when you are told.

01:35.847 --> 01:40.013
Do not speak unless spoken to,
do not move unless directed.

01:40.013 --> 01:43.447
Welcome to the Perfect School.

01:43.447 --> 01:45.313
[ Alarm Blaring ]

01:50.413 --> 01:53.347
No one's escaped
from the Perfect School.

01:53.347 --> 01:54.880
And no one ever will.

01:56.347 --> 01:58.913
This is your headmaster,
Mr. O'Connor.

01:58.913 --> 02:00.713
Open the door.

02:03.913 --> 02:06.447
- [ Trellis Snaps ]
- [ Grunts ]

02:06.447 --> 02:08.680
[ CJ ]
That was you last night, wasn't it?

02:08.680 --> 02:10.613
You were the one
who tried to escape.

02:13.713 --> 02:15.313
[ Thunderclap ]

02:15.747 --> 02:17.847
Mom, it's me.
You got to get me out of here.

02:18.347 --> 02:21.113
There's a lot of really freaky stuff
going on here.

02:22.113 --> 02:23.447
[ Muffled Cries ]

02:23.447 --> 02:25.647
Hello, Mrs. O'Connor,
this is the headmaster.

02:25.647 --> 02:26.580
I just want to reassure you

02:27.013 --> 02:29.080
that we're doing everything possible
to change Brian.

02:36.080 --> 02:38.247
[ Grunting ]

02:48.047 --> 02:49.747
[ Thunderclap ]

02:54.713 --> 02:58.247
- [ Metallic Clanking ]
- [ Footsteps Echoing ]

02:59.647 --> 03:01.613
[ Voices Echoing ]

03:23.213 --> 03:26.213
[ Doctor ]
Height, 64".

03:27.213 --> 03:29.047
Brown eyes, brown hair

03:31.447 --> 03:32.880
chin, 3".

03:41.147 --> 03:43.713
Chest is... chest, 37".

03:47.547 --> 03:49.880
Arm length, uh, 21".

03:49.880 --> 03:52.613
Brian, are you awake?

03:52.613 --> 03:55.913
Brian, you awake?
Brian. Brian, you awake?

03:56.580 --> 03:59.380
[ Grunting, Sighs ]

03:59.380 --> 04:01.147
Man, you totally overslept.

04:01.147 --> 04:04.280
You gotta be in class in 5 minutes.

04:04.280 --> 04:06.013
[ Footsteps Receding ]

04:07.013 --> 04:09.780
- [ Sighs ]
- [ Door Closes ]

04:11.213 --> 04:13.713
[ Birds Chirping ]

04:29.747 --> 04:31.713
[ Brian ]
They measured me, they weighed me.

04:32.480 --> 04:34.113
They took my fingerprints.

04:34.113 --> 04:37.613
Pretty weird dream, man.
You shouldn't eat before you go to bed.

04:37.613 --> 04:39.780
I don't know.
It didn't feel like a dream.

04:42.780 --> 04:44.280
Yeah, it's good.

04:44.780 --> 04:46.780
Heh, thanks.

04:49.280 --> 04:52.280
- How long did it take you to do this?
- About 3 hours.

04:53.280 --> 04:54.780
I like it. Great story.

04:54.780 --> 04:57.780
- Check out the teacher's pet.
- [ CJ Chuckles ]

04:59.247 --> 05:03.580
- Very good, Joe.
- May I go get a drink, please?

05:03.580 --> 05:04.330
Go.

05:06.413 --> 05:10.380
- That guy is a total kiss-up.
- You said it.

05:10.813 --> 05:12.680
No talking.

05:17.747 --> 05:20.213
[ Whispering ]
I bet he's a spy.

05:20.213 --> 05:22.447
I was thinking the same thing.

05:22.947 --> 05:24.480
That's it!

05:28.647 --> 05:31.147
[ Chair Creaking ]

05:44.447 --> 05:46.447
[ Children Chattering ]

05:54.380 --> 05:56.380
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

06:04.380 --> 06:05.847
[ Door Opens ]

06:06.847 --> 06:08.080
[ Door Closes ]

06:12.847 --> 06:15.980
What are you doing here?
They sent you to spy on me?

06:15.980 --> 06:18.413
Spy on you?
What are you talking about?

06:18.413 --> 06:20.947
I took too long getting a drink
and the guardian got mad.

06:20.947 --> 06:22.380
How stupid do you think I am?

06:22.880 --> 06:24.113
I don't know.
How stupid are you?

06:24.547 --> 06:27.880
You are not fooling anyone, OK?
Me and C.J. figured it out.

06:27.880 --> 06:29.380
Oh, you did, huh?

06:29.880 --> 06:32.380
Look, you think I've been all warm
and friendly with these guys

06:32.847 --> 06:34.280
'cause I'm working for them?

06:34.280 --> 06:36.880
Man, I'm a better actor
than I thought.

06:36.880 --> 06:37.847
What are you talking about?

06:37.847 --> 06:40.447
Ever heard the phrase:
"Go along to get along"?

06:41.080 --> 06:43.013
Can't say that I have.

06:43.013 --> 06:45.447
Look, they think I love it here.

06:45.447 --> 06:49.047
They say I'm the most cooperative
student they've ever had.

06:49.047 --> 06:50.047
And do you know what?

06:50.047 --> 06:52.047
I'm the last person
they'd ever expect

06:52.547 --> 06:53.980
expect to escape from this place.

06:53.980 --> 06:56.380
- You're gonna escape.
- Tonight.

06:56.380 --> 06:57.813
Want to come with me?

06:57.813 --> 07:00.780
Why? So you can rat on me?
Forget it.

07:00.780 --> 07:04.180
- I told you, I'm not on their side.
- [ Headmaster ] Brian O'Connor.

07:09.113 --> 07:14.413
You, I'd expect to see here.
But Joe... I'm surprised at you.

07:14.413 --> 07:19.013
You've made such tremendous
progress, unlike some.

07:27.580 --> 07:29.080
[ Door Closes ]

07:30.580 --> 07:32.080
[ Voices Echoing ]

08:05.513 --> 08:08.580
[ Voices Continue Echoing ]

08:09.013 --> 08:12.813
Hey. Hello. Where are you?

08:12.813 --> 08:14.813
[ Voices Echoing ]

08:28.280 --> 08:30.213
[ Computer Beeps ]

08:32.347 --> 08:33.847
There's gotta be a way out of here.

08:43.647 --> 08:46.847
[ Man On Walkie-Talkie ]
Unauthorized computer access in Section D.

08:47.247 --> 08:49.313
I'm on my way, over.

08:56.713 --> 08:58.180
[ Beeping ]

08:59.113 --> 09:01.447
Nursery?

09:03.280 --> 09:06.280
- [ Computer Beeps ]
- Access denied?

09:06.280 --> 09:08.713
- What are you guys hiding?
- [ Clacking ]

09:15.980 --> 09:18.713
OK.
Let's see what they got on me.

09:19.713 --> 09:21.213
[ Beeping ]

09:21.713 --> 09:23.180
[ Humming ]

09:44.680 --> 09:48.180
- [ Beeping ]
- 95 percent.

09:50.980 --> 09:52.880
I'm almost done?

10:03.613 --> 10:05.513
[ Doorknob Squeaking ]

10:18.013 --> 10:19.380
[ Doorknob Squeaking ]

10:38.847 --> 10:40.847
It's all clear.

10:43.413 --> 10:44.413
[ Computer Beeps ]

10:44.413 --> 10:47.780
It must have been
a system malfunction. Over.

10:51.413 --> 10:52.913
[ Sighs ]

11:02.980 --> 11:04.747
[ Clanking ]

11:14.913 --> 11:16.347
[ Ripping ]

11:16.347 --> 11:18.380
[ Grunts ]

11:21.347 --> 11:23.213
[ Sighs ]

11:35.247 --> 11:37.147
[ Sighing ]

11:45.480 --> 11:46.980
[ Panting ]

11:54.480 --> 11:55.947
Hmm.

11:56.947 --> 11:58.447
[ Clanking ]

12:03.080 --> 12:04.647
[ Grunts ]

12:05.147 --> 12:07.647
- ...OK?
- Yes, sir.

12:18.680 --> 12:20.713
[ Whispering ]
Psst, C.J.

12:21.113 --> 12:22.980
I thought you were
in the headmaster's office.

12:22.980 --> 12:25.647
I was.
I got to the computer system.

12:26.280 --> 12:27.213
- What?
- Yeah.

12:27.713 --> 12:29.213
And it said my program
was almost finished.

12:29.213 --> 12:31.347
Great. That means you
get to go home soon.

12:31.347 --> 12:34.513
Yeah, right. You seen what the kids
look like who come out of here?

12:35.213 --> 12:37.713
I don't wanna end up like that.
Do you?

12:38.580 --> 12:39.513
I gotta get out of here now.

12:40.247 --> 12:41.680
Well, if you're going,
I'm going with you.

12:41.680 --> 12:43.713
Cool.
I knew I could count on you.

12:43.713 --> 12:46.613
Meet me in the laundry room.
We'll hide in a pile of clothes.

12:46.613 --> 12:48.380
When they come to pick up
the laundry in the morning,

12:48.380 --> 12:49.913
they'll take us with them.

12:49.913 --> 12:51.413
It's like in the movies.

12:51.413 --> 12:54.047
They're gonna be looking for me.
I need a distraction.

12:55.880 --> 12:57.713
One distraction coming up.

12:58.113 --> 12:59.147
[ Boy ]
Hey!

12:59.947 --> 13:01.413
[ Bucket Falling ]

13:01.847 --> 13:04.613
- He did it.
- You! You're history!

13:05.047 --> 13:07.747
- [ CJ ] Fight, fight, fight!
- [ Boys Clamoring ]

13:08.247 --> 13:09.880
[ Guard ]
All you guys are going on report,

13:10.380 --> 13:13.880
- if you don't stop that right now!
- [ Clamoring Continues ]

13:22.847 --> 13:25.813
Now, as for you, Mr. O'Connor...

13:30.113 --> 13:34.413
- [ Door Creaking ]
- Sir, we have a fight in Sector A.

13:34.413 --> 13:36.413
Brian O'Connor.

13:38.313 --> 13:40.380
[ Crunching ]

13:57.780 --> 14:00.647
- He's got to be somewhere.
- Yeah. We'll find him.

14:04.713 --> 14:06.747
[ Footsteps Approaching ]

14:07.680 --> 14:09.813
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

14:09.813 --> 14:11.447
[ Panting ]

14:13.947 --> 14:15.447
[ Door Creaking ]

14:24.547 --> 14:27.547
[ Guard ] Section D all clear.
Now in Section E.

14:43.380 --> 14:45.280
[ Door Creaking ]

15:24.680 --> 15:26.680
[ Door Humming ]

15:40.247 --> 15:42.747
[ Grunts ]
What is this place?

15:54.547 --> 15:56.447
[ Bubbling ]

17:00.213 --> 17:03.213
- Brian, what's wrong?
- I know how they do it.

17:03.213 --> 17:05.713
- How they do what?
- How they create the perfect kid.

17:05.713 --> 17:06.713
They're cloning us.

17:07.213 --> 17:08.713
The voices.
They're the real kids.

17:09.213 --> 17:11.213
They must be locked away downstairs.

17:11.213 --> 17:13.213
They send the replacements
home with the parents.

17:13.213 --> 17:16.213
- That's impossible.
- No! No, it's not!

17:16.213 --> 17:18.213
They did it with
sheep over in Scotland.

17:18.213 --> 17:20.713
These guys,
they just took it a step further.

17:20.713 --> 17:23.713
- How do you know all this?
- I saw my clone.

17:23.713 --> 17:25.213
He's in a tank in there.

17:25.213 --> 17:28.213
They're growing him
right now to replace me.

17:28.213 --> 17:30.713
We can't wait for the laundry.
We got to go now.

17:30.713 --> 17:32.213
[ CJ ]
Come on, I think I know a way.

17:37.247 --> 17:39.747
- [ Brian ] Where are we going?
- Trust me.

17:46.413 --> 17:48.313
[ Beeping ]

17:48.313 --> 17:49.513
[ Buzzing ]

17:50.447 --> 17:53.647
- [ CJ ] You're not going anywhere.
- What?

17:53.647 --> 17:55.947
[ CJ ]
The laundry truck just left without you.

17:55.947 --> 17:57.947
Say hello to your new roommates

17:57.947 --> 18:00.947
you should be more careful
who you trust, Brian.

18:00.947 --> 18:03.513
You were watching me right
from the start, weren't you?

18:04.013 --> 18:06.347
Joe's not the spy, you are.

18:06.347 --> 18:07.647
Look on the bright side.

18:07.647 --> 18:10.313
Your parents are gonna get
what they always wanted.

18:10.313 --> 18:13.713
The perfect kid.
Your clone's almost ready.

18:14.947 --> 18:16.380
[ CJ Grunts ]

18:16.380 --> 18:18.747
- Get back here! No!
- [ Children Clamouring ]

18:18.747 --> 18:20.747
Let go of me! Get back here!

18:23.713 --> 18:27.547
Don't fight it, Brian.
It's good to be perfect.

18:39.347 --> 18:42.113
You're not going anywhere.

18:43.047 --> 18:45.980
Except back to the lock up
with the rest of them.

18:47.347 --> 18:49.347
[ Laughing ]

18:53.347 --> 18:54.847
[ Mom ]
Anyone for more desert?

18:55.347 --> 18:57.847
- [ Dad ] Oh, not me. I'm stuffed.
- Riley.

18:57.847 --> 19:00.347
- No, thanks, Mom.
- Brian!

19:00.347 --> 19:02.847
No, thanks, Mom.
That was a wonderful dinner.

19:02.847 --> 19:03.847
Can I help you with the dishes?

19:04.513 --> 19:06.980
I can't get over the change in you.

19:06.980 --> 19:09.480
No, thanks, honey.
That's OK. I'll get them.

19:10.913 --> 19:13.080
May I please be excused?

19:13.080 --> 19:15.080
You may.

19:19.380 --> 19:22.713
Let me know if you need any help
with your homework.

19:22.713 --> 19:24.947
I liked him better the other way.

19:24.947 --> 19:26.947
[ Door Humming ]

19:28.447 --> 19:30.947
[ Children Clamoring ]
Food!

19:32.947 --> 19:34.447
[ Boy ]
I'm so hungry.

19:34.447 --> 19:35.947
[ Boy ]
Come on, just give us something.

19:35.947 --> 19:39.447
You got to get me out of here.
I keep telling you.

19:39.447 --> 19:41.813
The real Brian shoved me
in here and took my spot.

19:41.813 --> 19:45.280
I am the clone.
Brian O'Connor's clone!

19:45.780 --> 19:48.280
Yeah. I'm a clone, too. Come on,
you got to get me out of here.

19:48.280 --> 19:49.680
Come on, please.

19:49.680 --> 19:51.047
You got to get me out of here.
I'm Joe Roberts' clone!

19:51.780 --> 19:53.213
We're all clones.
Let us all out!

19:53.213 --> 19:55.713
We're all clones.
We are!

19:55.713 --> 19:57.713
[ All Clamoring ]

19:59.713 --> 20:03.113
- [ Boy ] We want to sleep!
- [ Boys Crying ]

20:03.113 --> 20:04.613
[ All Clamoring ]

20:06.113 --> 20:08.613
Nice try.

20:18.113 --> 20:20.113
I'm stuck.

20:20.113 --> 20:24.613
- What happened?
- Someone put glue on my chair.

20:24.613 --> 20:27.613
Really? Why would someone
do that on purpose?

20:27.613 --> 20:31.113
- Must have been an accident.
- [ Sighs ]

20:40.480 --> 20:42.313
Operation rescue.

20:42.813 --> 20:45.847
Don't worry, guys.
I'll get you out of there.

20:45.847 --> 20:49.447
If it's the last thing I do,
I'll get you out of there.

